Use the standard library
This is how to minPath of grid and k:
   Remember that rows is grid's length
   Remember that cols is item 0 in grid's length

   Remember that best is []
   Remember that bestSum is 0
   Remember that started is no

   Remember that start is 0
   Do this rows times:
      Remember that path is []
      Remember that total is 0
      Remember that r is start
      Remember that c is 0

      Do this k times:
         When r is at least (diff of rows and 1), then:
            When c is at least (diff of cols and 1), then:
               Add path to (sum of r and 1)
               Remember that total is sum of total and item c in item r in grid
            End when
         End when

         When c is less than (diff of cols and 1), then:
            Increase c
         But, if not:
            When r is less than (diff of rows and 1), then:
               Increase r
            End when
         End when
      End do

      When started is no, then:
         Remember that best is path
         Remember that bestSum is total
         Remember that started is yes
      But, if not:
         When total is less than bestSum, then:
            Remember that best is path
            Remember that bestSum is total
         End when
      End when

      Increase start
      When start is more than (diff of rows and k), then:
         Leave the loop
      End when
   End do

   The answer is best
Now you know